Friends and relatives of controversial businessman Gavin Watson gathered in Johannesburg on Friday to pay their last respects to him. The former Bosasa CEO died in a car crash near OR Tambo International Airport on Monday. Bosasa is now known as African Global Operations. The company has been implicated in testimony at the state capture inquiry as having been involved in bribery and corruption. Valance Watson kicked off his eulogy by lambasting the media for its treatment of his brother. "Journalists tell you that I am a liar, but history is written by journalists who have hung heroes," he said.  GET THE NEWS at your fingertips and download the News24 app for Android here now. Get it for your iPhone here. KEEP UPDATED on the latest news by subscribing to our FREE newsletter. - FOLLOW News24 on Twitter  